  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Computing the information dimension <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>I</mi></mrow></msub></math> of a complex network <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi mathvariant="script">G</mi></math> requires covering <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi mathvariant="script">G</mi></math> by a minimal collection of “boxes” of size s to obtain a set of probabilities, computing the entropy <math altimg="si29.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>H</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>s</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> , and quantifying how <math altimg="si29.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>H</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>s</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> scales with <math altimg="si4.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi mathvariant="normal">log</mi><mo>⁡</mo><mi>s</mi></math> . We show that to determine whether <math altimg="si5.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>I</mi></mrow></msub><mo>≤</mo><msub><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub></math> holds for <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi mathvariant="script">G</mi></math> , where <math altimg="si7.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub></math> is the box counting dimension, it is not sufficient to determine a minimal covering for each s . We introduce the new notion of a maximal entropy minimal covering of <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi mathvariant="script">G</mi></math> , and a corresponding new definition of <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>I</mi></mrow></msub></math> . The use of maximal entropy minimal coverings in many cases enhances the ability to compute <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>I</mi></mrow></msub></math> .</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">Elsevier</subfield>
  </datafield>
